> >>Is it my double relay, my AFM or what....  Full tank of gas just 1.5miles
> >back.
>
> The AFM is just the switch. You should check the output from the relay at
> 88d and the voltage from the battery at 88y and 88z:
>
> http://www.ratwell.com/technical/DoubleRelay/Wiring.jpg
>
> 85 - Ground
> 86 - Thermo time switch and ECU pin 4
> 86a - Starter
> 86b - AFM harness connector #36
> 86c - Terminal 15 of ignition coil (+12v)
> 88a - AFM harness connector #39
> 88b - Series resistors and ECU pin 10
> 88c - Aux air regulator
> 88d - Fuel Pump
> 88y - Battery +12v
> 88z - Battery +12v
>
> --
> Richard, 1978 Westfalia CDN
> http://www.ratwell.com/
> Cupertino, CA
